<Layout title="Compliance" description="701am Compliance — SOC 2, FERPA, GDPR, and regulatory information.">
<div class="ph">
  <p class="ey">Compliance</p>
  <h1><span class="g">Compliance</span></h1>
  <p>701am is designed from the ground up to meet the compliance and security requirements of higher education institutions.</p>
</div>

<article class="legal">
<h2>FERPA</h2>
<p>701am is designed to support institutional compliance with the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA). We do not access, store, or process student educational records unless explicitly authorized by the institution. Our data processing agreements reflect FERPA requirements.</p>

<h2>GDPR</h2>
<p>For users in the European Union, 701am complies with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Data subject rights — including access, correction, deletion, and portability — can be exercised by contacting privacy@701am.com.</p>

<h2>SOC 2</h2>
<p>Our cloud infrastructure provider (AWS) maintains SOC 2 Type II certification. We align our internal controls with SOC 2 principles. A current SOC 2 report is available upon request under NDA.</p>

<h2>Data Residency</h2>
<p>By default, customer data is stored in the United States (us-east-1). Alternative data residency options may be available upon request.</p>
</article>
</Layout>
